listing.description:
# Plan, Track and Report anything
The [placker power-up](https://help.placker.com/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up) is created by experienced project and program managers with input from hundreds of teams that already use this power-up every day to save time, avoid mistakes and get projects done with Trello.

## Plan more effectively
- Gantt charts will help you to visually plan cards and create dependencies between the cards, also across multiple boards.
- Use card count, story points or effort to plan your work and understand how the workload is planned by viewing it by member, list, label, milestone or board.

## Track smarter
- Placker automatically tracks the progress of your cards ( from open to completed) when you move your cards between the lists (or assign labels).
- We will capture the actual start and end date and calculate the effort spent on a card so you capture exactly how your cards are being completed, without any additional effort.

## Report in real-time
- Dashboards will tell everything you and your team need to on top of your projects,  which cards are overdue, who has to many open cards or the expected completion date based on your throughput.
- Create (real-time) dashboards to monitor and report the status of your cards.
- Customize your dashboard by using a library of widgets that support the Agile, Scrum and traditional project management methodologies.

## For any type of project or process
- When you work with Agile you can using story points, sprint burndown chart, completion chart, cumulative flow chart and control charts.
- When you work with Scrum you can  use cycle and lead time trackers, throughput overviews and  time to market.
- When you work with a more traditional methodology we have the trackers to monitor scope, time, effort, budget and risks.

## Works across and between boards and teams
- View and combine any number of boards on the Gantt, board or dashboards.
- Export your data to a spreadsheet or MS project file
- Import your changes from a excel spreadsheet or Microsoft project file
- Create card mirrors between boards to keep cards synchronized automatically.

### Add plan attributes to Trello
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/Project-by-placker-overview.png)
[Read more about the power-up](https://help.placker.com/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up)

### Use Gantt charts
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/placker-gantt-landing.png)
[Learn more about our gantt chart](http://ganttfortrello.com)

### Use dashboards
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/placker-track-landing.png)
Dashboards are perfect to show the status full screen on a TV

### Create card mirrors between boards to keep cards synchornized
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/placker-mirror-boards.gif)

### One-click access to your Gantt chart from Trello
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/placker-power-up-gantt.gif)

### One-click access to your dashboard from Trello
![screenshot](https://placker.com/power-up/screenshots/placker-power-up-track.gif)

### Learn more
Created by [placker.com](https://placker.com).
Vist our [help center](https://help.placker.com/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up/projects-by-placker-trello-power-up) for help and support.
Placker has a 15 day free trail and requires a [paid subscription](https://placker.com/pricing) afterwards.
